TITLE: Initialize Application-Wide Logic Outside React Components
DESCRIPTION: This code snippet demonstrates how to run essential application initialization logic, such as checking authentication tokens or loading data from local storage, only once when the application starts. By placing this code outside any React component and verifying the `window` object's existence, it ensures execution only in the browser environment and independently of component lifecycles.

SOURCE: https://react.dev/learn/synchronizing-with-effects

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
if (typeof window !== 'undefined') { // Check if we're running in the browser.  
  checkAuthToken();  
  loadDataFromLocalStorage();  
}  

function App() {  
  // ...  
}
```

