TITLE: Avoid: Running initialization logic in React useEffect (development double-run)
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates an anti-pattern where application-wide initialization logic is placed in a `useEffect` hook in the top-level `App` component. In development mode, React's Strict Mode will cause this `useEffect` to run twice, potentially leading to issues like invalidating authentication tokens or duplicate data loading.

SOURCE: https://react.dev/learn/you-might-not-need-an-effect

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
function App() {  
  // ðŸ”´ Avoid: Effects with logic that should only ever run once  
  useEffect(() => {  
    loadDataFromLocalStorage();  
    checkAuthToken();  
  }, []);  
  // ...  
}
```

